<subSubSection pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="54.[151,1437,259,1906]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,259,285]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Recognized by following set of features: dorsum dark brown-black (
<figureCitation box="[1053,1135,259,286]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-27@24.[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal habitus photographs. a. Peltidocylapus rugosus (lectotype); b. Peltidocylapus scutellaris (♂, Costa Rica); c. Peltidocylapus simplex (holotype); d. Peltidocylapus spinosus (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760402/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 6c</figureCitation>
); antennal segment II dark brown, tinged with dark yellow basally and with white annulation on apex that is much narrower than half of interocular distance (
<figureCitation box="[366,448,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-27@24.[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal habitus photographs. a. Peltidocylapus rugosus (lectotype); b. Peltidocylapus scutellaris (♂, Costa Rica); c. Peltidocylapus simplex (holotype); d. Peltidocylapus spinosus (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760402/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 6c</figureCitation>
); posterior lobe with strongly developed swelling medially (
<figureCitation box="[1127,1210,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-27@24.[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal habitus photographs. a. Peltidocylapus rugosus (lectotype); b. Peltidocylapus scutellaris (♂, Costa Rica); c. Peltidocylapus simplex (holotype); d. Peltidocylapus spinosus (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760402/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 6c</figureCitation>
); scutellum covered with long, erect setae, with strongly convex, longitudinal swelling medially (
<figureCitation box="[1006,1088,367,394]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-27@24.[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal habitus photographs. a. Peltidocylapus rugosus (lectotype); b. Peltidocylapus scutellaris (♂, Costa Rica); c. Peltidocylapus simplex (holotype); d. Peltidocylapus spinosus (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760402/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 6c</figureCitation>
); endosoma membranous, with large sclerotized, serrate lobe beneath sclerotized distal portion of ductus seminis (dss) (
<figureCitation box="[1137,1262,403,430]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Figs 14l–n</figureCitation>
); dss broad and long, caliciform, with broad, weakly sclerotized, transparent portion dorsally (Fig; 14l); sclerotized plate on base of dss rather small, elliptical (Fig; 14l); left paramere apical process without any outgrowth (
<figureCitation box="[1213,1353,475,502]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Figs. 14o, p</figureCitation>
); bursa copulatrix sclerotized rings large (
<figureCitation box="[534,657,511,538]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="51.[151,250,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[163,1373,207,1585]" captionTargetId="figure-15@51.[152,1435,181,1585]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 19. Female genitalia. a, b, d, e. Bursa copulatrix (dorsal view); c. Ventral labiate plate (ventral view, with remainder of bursa copulatrix dissected); f, g. Bursa copulatrix, posterior wall. a–c. Peltidocylapus parallelus; d, e, f. Peltidocylapus simplex; g. Cylapus tenuicornis. dlp = dorsal labiate plate; odl = lateral oviduct; sd = seminal depository; sg = spermathecal gland; sr = sclerotized ring; vlp = ventral labiate plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760444" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760444/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 19d, e</figureCitation>
); ventral labiate plate with broad, irregularly shaped sclerotization.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="54.[151,1437,259,1906]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,547,573]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Description.</emphasis>
Male. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[424,616,547,573]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">COLORATION</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[632,714,547,574]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-27@24.[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal habitus photographs. a. Peltidocylapus rugosus (lectotype); b. Peltidocylapus scutellaris (♂, Costa Rica); c. Peltidocylapus simplex (holotype); d. Peltidocylapus spinosus (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760402/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 6c</figureCitation>
). Dorsum dark brownish black. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1076,1138,547,574]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Head</emphasis>
. Fuscous tinged with dark yellow; antennal segment I dark stramineous; segment II dark brown, tinged with dark yellow basally and with white annulation on apex that is much narrower than half of interocular distance; segments III and IV dark brown; labium varying from fuscous dark yellow, tinged with red to entirely black. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1004,1090,655,682]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Thorax</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1104,1215,656,681]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Pronotum</emphasis>
. Varying from dark brown to black. 
<emphasis box="[337,642,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Mesoscutum and scutellum</emphasis>
. Mesoscutum varying from dark castaneous to black; scutellum varying from dark brown castaneous with two large dark yellow patches each situated baso-laterally to entirely black, apex with small dark yellow spot. 
<emphasis box="[540,722,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Thoracic pleura</emphasis>
. Proepimeron and proepisternum dark brown to black; remaining pleura dark brown. 
<emphasis box="[417,548,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Hemelytron</emphasis>
. Dark brown; cuneus tinged with red basally; membrane dark grey. 
<emphasis box="[1320,1373,800,825]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Legs</emphasis>
. Procoxa dark castaneous to black; meso- and metacoxae varying from yellow to dark yellow tinged with dark brown basally; proleg dark brown with more or dark yellow annulation subapically. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1030,1140,871,898]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Varying from castaneous with yellow areas to entirely black. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[561,934,907,933]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">TEXTURE AND VESTITURE</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[951,1034,907,934]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-27@24.[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal habitus photographs. a. Peltidocylapus rugosus (lectotype); b. Peltidocylapus scutellaris (♂, Costa Rica); c. Peltidocylapus simplex (holotype); d. Peltidocylapus spinosus (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760402/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 6c</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1056,1142,907,934]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Thorax</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1157,1267,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Scutellum</emphasis>
. Covered with long, erect setae. 
<emphasis box="[345,476,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Hemelytron</emphasis>
. Covered with dense, semi-recumbent and erect setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1091,1264,943,969]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">STRUCTURE</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1279,1360,943,970]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-27@24.[151,1435,181,1465]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal habitus photographs. a. Peltidocylapus rugosus (lectotype); b. Peltidocylapus scutellaris (♂, Costa Rica); c. Peltidocylapus simplex (holotype); d. Peltidocylapus spinosus (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760402/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 6c</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Thorax</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[205,316,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Pronotum</emphasis>
. Posterior lobe with strongly developed swelling medially. 
<emphasis box="[990,1100,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Scutellum</emphasis>
. With strongly convex, broad longitudinal swelling medially. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[511,621,1015,1042]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Abdomen</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[637,743,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Genitalia</emphasis>
. Endosoma membranous, with large sclerotized, serrate lobe beneath sclerotized distal portion of ductus seminis (dss) (
<figureCitation box="[825,994,1051,1078]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Figs 14l, m, n</figureCitation>
); dss broad and long, caliciform, with broad, weakly sclerotized, transparent portion dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[784,910,1087,1114]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Figs 14l, n</figureCitation>
); sclerotized plate on base of dss rather small, elliptical (
<figureCitation box="[265,356,1123,1150]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 14l</figureCitation>
); left paramere C-shaped, apical process without lateral outgrowth (
<figureCitation box="[1120,1250,1123,1150]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Figs 14o, p</figureCitation>
); right paramere sickle-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[319,417,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 14q</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[151,1437,259,1906]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
Female. Like male in coloration, structure, texture, and vestiture. 
<emphasis box="[934,1048,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Genitalia.</emphasis>
Bursa copulatrix trapezoidal (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="51.[151,250,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[163,1373,207,1585]" captionTargetId="figure-15@51.[152,1435,181,1585]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 19. Female genitalia. a, b, d, e. Bursa copulatrix (dorsal view); c. Ventral labiate plate (ventral view, with remainder of bursa copulatrix dissected); f, g. Bursa copulatrix, posterior wall. a–c. Peltidocylapus parallelus; d, e, f. Peltidocylapus simplex; g. Cylapus tenuicornis. dlp = dorsal labiate plate; odl = lateral oviduct; sd = seminal depository; sg = spermathecal gland; sr = sclerotized ring; vlp = ventral labiate plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760444" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760444/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Figs 19d, e</figureCitation>
); sclerotized rings large, kidney-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[698,831,1231,1258]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="51.[151,250,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[163,1373,207,1585]" captionTargetId="figure-15@51.[152,1435,181,1585]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 19. Female genitalia. a, b, d, e. Bursa copulatrix (dorsal view); c. Ventral labiate plate (ventral view, with remainder of bursa copulatrix dissected); f, g. Bursa copulatrix, posterior wall. a–c. Peltidocylapus parallelus; d, e, f. Peltidocylapus simplex; g. Cylapus tenuicornis. dlp = dorsal labiate plate; odl = lateral oviduct; sd = seminal depository; sg = spermathecal gland; sr = sclerotized ring; vlp = ventral labiate plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760444" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760444/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Figs 19d, e</figureCitation>
); ventral labiate plate with broad, irregularly shaped sclerotization.
</paragraph>
