<paragraph blockId="54.[151,1437,259,1906]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1627,1653]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wolski" authorityYear="2021" box="[321,434,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Peltidocylapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis box="[321,434,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">P. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most like 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wolski" authorityYear="2021" box="[572,746,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Peltidocylapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ecuadorensis">
<emphasis box="[572,746,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">P. ecuadorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by possessing long setae on the scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[1227,1316,1627,1654]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[169,1418,181,1798]" captionTargetId="figure-27@32.[169,1418,181,1798]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 11. Scanning electron micrographs. a, e, g, m. Dorsal habitus; b, n. Lateral habitus; h, l. Scutellum; c, f, i. Thoracic pleura; d, j, o. Tarsus. k. Pretarsal claw. a–d. Cylapinus minusculus; e, f. Cylapoides unicolor; g–j. Peltidocylapus caudatus; k. Peltidocylapus calyciformis; l. Peltidocylapus ecuadorensis; m–o. Peltidocylapus scutellaris." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760418" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760418/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 11l</figureCitation>
). In can be easily distinguished by the left paramere apical process devoid of an outgrowth (
<figureCitation box="[1053,1183,1663,1690]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[289,1308,181,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-27@44.[229,1359,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia. a, f, l, r. Endosoma (dorsal view); b, h, n. Endosoma (ventral view); g, m. Endosoma (right lateral view); c, i, o, s. Left paramere (right lateral view). d, j, p, t. Left paramere (dorsal view). e, k, q, u. Right paramere (left lateral view). a–e. Peltidocylapus rugosus; f–k. Peltidocylapus scutellaris; l–k. Peltidocylapus simplex; r–u. Peltidocylapus spinosus. dss = distal part of ductus seminis inside endosoma. Scale bars 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5760428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5760428/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Figs 14o, p</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
